# Copy to auth.users and add real credentials when enabling LAN access.
# One username:password per line. Lines starting with # are ignored.
# Passwords may contain colons — only the first colon separates user from pass.
#
# Or set the same pairs in .env instead (comma-separated, no spaces):
#   BOOKKING_AUTH_USERS=admin:secret,phone:other-secret
#
# When any users are configured, the browser will prompt for a login.
# All users share the same ledger — this is access control, not separate books.

admin:change-me
